Demonstration that awk's CSV support.

```{r setup, echo=FALSE}
library(knitrengines)
```

Use an old friend:

```{r mtcars}
write.csv(mtcars, "mtcars.csv", row.names = FALSE)
```

```{cawk, mtcars-awk-block, awk.csv=TRUE}
#| awk.var.mpg: 1
#| awk.var.cyl: 2
#| awk.var.disp: 3
#| awk.var.hp: 4
#| awk.var.drat: 5
#| awk.var.wt: 6
#| awk.var.qsec: 7
#| awk.var.vs: 8
#| awk.var.am: 9
#| awk.var.gear: 10
#| awk.var.carb: 11
#| awk.file.1: "mtcars.csv"
NR > 1 { 
  cum_mpg_by[$cyl] += $mpg
} END { 
  for (cyl in cum_mpg_by) 
    print cyl " => " cum_mpg_by[cyl] 
}
```

```{r cleanup}
file.remove("mtcars.csv")
```
